What is JPA? &ldquo;The Java Persistence API is the Java API for the management of persistence and object/relational mapping in Java EE and Java SE environments. It provides an object/relational mapping facility for the Java application developer using a Java domain model to manage a relational database.&rdquo;
It&rsquo;s quoted from JSR(Java Specification Request) managed by Java Community Process.
This is just the definition of what&rsquo;s JPA, let&rsquo;s recall how we persist data before adopting JPA.
